{
  "texts": [
    "However, researchers should be aware that active learning algorithms rely on previous classification decisions and prioritize studies with similar study designs or conceptual frameworks to previously identified relevant studies.",
    "Therefore, there is a risk of overlooking studies that differ methodologically or conceptually from previously identified relevant studies.",
    "Improving our understanding of how learning algorithms deal with the diverse methodological and conceptual approaches in educational psychology research is critical.",
    "Third, researchers should be critical of using abstract screening tools with black boxes or out-of-the-box solutions.",
    "The selection of a learning algorithm and stopping criteria impacts the percentage of relevant studies in the abstract screening phase."
  ]
}